B tech in USA: Best Universities, Eligibility, Admission Requirements, Courses, Scholarships, Jobs

  • 206 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 15,2023 05:09 PM IST

B.Tech in USA is a four-year course, commonly known as Bachelor of Engineering (BE) or Bachelor of Science Engineering (B. Sc. Eng.). Read the blog to know the program details, including top universities, eligibility, admission process, scholarship options, etc.

Pursuing a Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) in the United States offers immense opportunities and challenges. USA is one of the preferred places among international students for its world-class education offered at state-of-the-art campuses. As per U.S. News, over 50% of international graduates enrol in an engineering course in the USA.

Offered as a four-year course, B.Tech in USA is generally referred to as Bachelor of Science Engineering (BSc. Eng.) or Bachelor of Engineering (BE). Out of 500 top engineering and technology schools in the world, more than 100 are in the USA.

To know more about the course, continue reading the blog.

Why Study B.Tech in USA?

Applying for B.Tech degree in the USA offers many career opportunities beyond quality education. Here are some of the reasons behind choosing this country as a study destination:

  • The USA houses some of the most prestigious globally recognised educational institutions known for their excellence in technology and engineering, ensuring students receive a quality education that is respected worldwide.
  • US universities emphasise providing students with research opportunities and classroom learning to help students learn and contribute to cutting-edge technology advancements. Many also offer students chances to participate in research projects, internships, and cooperative programs.
  • B.Tech courses in the USA are offered with various specialisations, including some emerging fields such as AI, Data Science, and Biomedical Engineering.
  • Similar to other developed nations, US institutions focus heavily on a practical approach to learning, encouraging students to engage in practical projects, labs, and real-world applications of their studies.
  • To reduce the financial burden of studying in the USA, the government and educational institutions offer many scholarships and financial aid programs to deserving and needy students.
  • Graduating from a US university also opens doors to job opportunities in some of the renowned tech giants, including Google, Apple, and Microsoft, as well as a multitude of startups and SMEs.
  • Programs like Optional Practical Training (OPT) allow students to gain work experience after graduation in their field of study, further enhancing the career prospects of international students.
  • Studying abroad allows international students to interact with peers from diverse backgrounds, enriching their overall learning experience and personal growth.

Types of Engineering Degrees in USA

The U.S. education system offers a broad spectrum of specialisations under B.Tech, including traditional branches like Mechanical, Civil, and Electrical Engineering, as well as emerging fields like Artificial Intelligence, Data Science, and Biomedical Engineering.

The B.Tech curriculum in U.S. universities typically includes a mix of core courses, electives, labs, and often an independent capstone project or research. This balance provides students with a comprehensive understanding of their field while enabling them to tailor their education to their specific interests. Students applying to study Engineering in USA can choose from the types of degree options:

  • Bachelor of Engineering (B.Eng.)
  • Bachelor of Engineering Science (B.Eng.Sc.)
  • Bachelor of Science Engineering (B.Sc.Eng.)
  • Bachelor of Science in Engineering (B.S.E.)/ Bachelor of Applied Science (B.A.Sc.)

These are offered across a wide spectrum of subject areas, including Bioengineering, Energy Engineering, Chemical Engineering, Civil and Structural Engineering, Nuclear Engineering, Electrical Engineering & Computer Sciences, Engineering Mathematics & Statistics, Engineering Physics, Environmental Engineering Science, Mechanical Engineering, etc.

B.Tech in USA: Admission Process

Thousands of students make applications to study in top universities and colleges of USA. Therefore, to stay ahead of the competition, students are advised to get details all the necessary details and make timely application.

Steps to apply for B.Tech in USA

  • Before applying, search and shortlist universities that match your interest and other needs
  • Give all the necessary standardised tests required for admission
  • Collect all the documents required to make an application
  • Get all the credentials evaluated through globally recognised agencies like WES or ECE
  •  Make an online application for B.Tech in the university of choice

Eligibility and Admission Requirements

Admission into USA universities requires a complete profile, presenting academic excellence, standardised test scores, personal essays and letter of recommendation. International students must also prove their English proficiency through TOEFL or IELTS.

Academic requirements typically include a high school diploma with Mathematics and Science. Most universities require SAT scores, while engineering programs often require or recommend SAT subject tests in Mathematics and Physics.

B.Tech in USA: Scholarships

The US offers a limited number of scholarships specific to engineering disciplines to international students. However, there are various scholarships that can be availed at bachelor level, irrespective of the stream. Here are some options that can be availed by international students to make their education affordable:

  • QS scholarships
  • Endowed Undergraduate Scholarship Funds
  • Ford Undergrad Engineer Scholarship
  • International Education Fee Scholarship
  • VueVille Future Technology Scholarship
  • BrokerFish International student scholarship

Additionally, organisations like the American Association of University Women (AAUW) and the Institute of International Education (IIE) offer scholarships.

Jobs and Career Opportunities

The USA is home to a plethora of tech companies, offering ample job opportunities to engineering graduates. Some of the trending job roles that students can opt post the completion of their study are:

  • Staff Engineer
  • Civil Engineer
  • Design Engineer
  • Process Engineer
  • Software Engineer
  • Software Developer
  • Project Engineer
  • Project Manager
  • Environmental Engineer
  • Senior Software Engineer
  • Mechanical Engineer
  •  Electrical Engineer
  • Manufacturing Engineer
  • Aerospace Engineer
  • Industrial Engineer
  • Chemical Engineer
  • Automation Engineering Manager

Conclusion
Pursuing a B.Tech degree in the USA can open doors to a plethora of career options for international students. While the journey requires significant preparation and investment, the returns can be truly transformative.

FAQ

What is the average cost of studying B.Tech in the USA?
The overall cost of pursuing B.Tech in USA includes both education and living expenses. The approximately B.Tech cost in the USA ranges from USD$ 45,000 to USD$ 60,000, based on the university student gets accepted into.
What are the eligibility requirements for pursuing a B.Tech degree in the USA?
The eligibility criteria for certain universities may differ from other universities, but a general requirement is to complete a high school education or its equivalent. Students may also need to provide standardised test scores like the SAT or ACT together with English language proficiency exams like the TOEFL or IELTS.
What are the popular B.Tech courses offered by universities in the USA?
Universities in the USA offer a wide range of B.Tech courses across various engineering disciplines. Some popular fields of study include Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, Chemical Engineering, Biomedical Engineering, and Civil Engineering. Students can choose specialisation based on their interests and career goals.
Are scholarships available for international students pursuing B.Tech degrees in the USA?
Yes, there several scholarships available for international students based on their merit and need, along with some offered specifically for international students. Many universities and external organisations offer scholarships to help offset tuition costs.
What are the job prospects for B.Tech graduates in the USA?
B.Tech graduates have promising job prospects in the USA as the engineering field offers various employment opportunities across various industries, including technology, manufacturing, healthcare, aerospace, energy, and more.
